{
  "text": "A Ljung-Box Q test [CITATION_1] ) was used to test if any autocorrelations remained in the residuals of the first 100 data points after estimating the parameters of the GLM. Every lag up to 20 volumes was tested. The proportion of voxels rejecting the null hypothesis, of no correlation at any lag, was calculated, with significance defined as p < .05 after false discovery rate correction for multiple comparison.",
